+## Concurrency Model
+
+### How Many Workflows Can Run Simultaneously?
+
+**Answer: As many as Node.js can handle.** Each `drive()` loop is:
+- One `run()` call (CPU: <10ms ظ¤ ONBAS is pure synchronous, ODS dispatches fire-and-forget)
+- One `sleep()` (I/O: 100ms-10s, yielded to event loop)
+- Filesystem reads/writes (I/O: yielded)
+
+The Node.js event loop handles many concurrent `drive()` loops naturally. They're cooperative ظ¤ each yields during sleep and I/O.
+
+```
+Timeline showing 3 concurrent workflows:
+
+Event Loop: ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظْ time
+             ظ¤é                    ظ¤é                    ظ¤é
+WF-1: run()ظ¤ظ¤sleep(100ms)ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤run()ظ¤ظ¤sleep(10s)ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤run()ظ¤ظ¤
+WF-2: ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤run()ظ¤ظ¤sleep(100ms)ظ¤ظ¤run()ظ¤ظ¤sleep(100ms)ظ¤ظ¤run()ظ¤ظ¤sleepظ¤ظ¤
+WF-3: ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤run()ظ¤ظ¤sleep(10s)ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤ظ¤run()ظ¤ظ¤
+
+No thread contention. No mutex. Just the event loop.
+```
+
+### What If Two Workflows Are In The Same Worktree?
+
+Works fine ظ¤ different graphSlugs, different state files, different pod sessions. The compound key `worktreePath:graphSlug` keeps them isolated.
+
+### What If Someone Calls start() Twice?
+
+Step 3 of `start()`: if the key already exists with status `'running'`, return `{ already: true }`. Idempotent.
